Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.08,0:00:12.61,Default,Tsujii,0000,0000,0000,,We've gotta get out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.00,0:01:04.04,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.67,0:01:16.76,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,I don't wanna die!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.51,0:01:27.32,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,This is not normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.90,0:01:58.15,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.76,0:02:00.76,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Has everyone lost their minds?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.89,0:02:15.24,Default,Arita,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Chibiki!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.13,0:02:17.98,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody else made it here?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.15,0:02:20.78,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Ow...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.78,0:02:22.99,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,The bleeding has stopped. \NIt's not serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.65,0:02:25.74,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,You all stay here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.74,0:02:26.54,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.36,0:02:32.33,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Matsui!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.90,0:02:33.77,Default,Matsui,0000,0000,0000,,Hel—
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.70,0:02:47.00,Default,Kazami,0000,0000,0000,,Sakakibara.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.75,0:02:50.02,Default,Kazami,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember this girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.02,0:02:51.19,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I do!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.19,0:02:53.94,Default,Kazami,0000,0000,0000,,Damn, I was wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.94,0:02:55.94,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Wrong? What are you saying?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.66,0:03:00.31,Default,Kazami,0000,0000,0000,,Sugiura said it was Misaki,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.31,0:03:04.24,Default,Kazami,0000,0000,0000,,but I think the dead one is you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.44,0:03:08.04,Default,Kazami,0000,0000,0000,,It started in May this year, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.29,0:03:12.21,Default,Kazami,0000,0000,0000,,So the one who joined the class \Nin May is obviously the dead one.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.14,0:03:18.13,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,You're wrong! It started in April!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.74,0:03:21.06,Default,Kazami,0000,0000,0000,,You expect me to believe that bullshit?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.77,0:03:41.28,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you doing this?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.96,0:03:44.96,Default,Kazami,0000,0000,0000,,I figured it out when \NTeshigawara almost killed me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.96,0:03:48.93,Default,Kazami,0000,0000,0000,,I have to send the dead back \Nto death, or else I'll die.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.93,0:03:49.79,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,But that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.79,0:03:50.95,Default,Kazami,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.95,0:03:52.35,Default,Kazami,0000,0000,0000,,If you hadn't come here,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.35,0:03:54.01,Default,Kazami,0000,0000,0000,,Yukari wouldn't have died!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.01,0:03:55.58,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Sakuragi?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.58,0:03:59.00,Default,Kazami,0000,0000,0000,,If you hadn't gotten close \Nto the nonexistent girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.71,0:04:04.89,Default,Kazami,0000,0000,0000,,Send the dead back to—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.07,0:04:15.60,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot. Kouichi isn't dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.34,0:04:20.11,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,But you've killed two people.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.36,0:04:22.47,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,You don't deserve to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.21,0:04:24.45,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,I'll help you die.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.59,0:04:27.92,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Keep Yukari company.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.09,0:04:34.70,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Classmates shouldn't be doing stupid things
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.70,0:04:36.67,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,like killing each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.49,0:04:40.14,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Pretty words.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.14,0:04:41.68,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,But someone who ran away
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.68,0:04:43.90,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,to watch from the sidelines, \Nbecause he was afraid to die,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.90,0:04:45.91,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,has no right to say anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.91,0:04:47.87,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,You're right. I ran away.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.36,0:04:50.81,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,But I can still save \Na student who's about
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.81,0:04:52.27,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,to die needlessly right in front of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.27,0:04:54.71,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,A spectator like you can't do anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.71,0:04:55.84,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,You can't change a thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.84,0:04:59.61,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,The only ones who can fix this \Nare those living in death's jaws!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.94,0:05:09.49,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Sakakibara, get outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.53,0:05:14.66,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Kazami?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.07,0:05:17.62,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Kazami!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.62,0:05:18.50,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.96,0:05:21.72,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.30,0:05:24.27,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Come on...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.12,0:05:27.21,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Stop messing around. Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.56,0:05:31.28,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.28,0:05:34.78,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it! Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.08,0:05:52.83,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Misaki's still inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.49,0:05:59.47,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Misaki! If you're here, answer me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.92,0:06:28.86,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.79,0:06:35.75,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Please, stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.38,0:06:40.77,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,If I don't kill her, we'll all die!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.77,0:06:42.44,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,You could die, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.44,0:06:45.24,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,You've got it all wrong! \NMisaki's not dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.64,0:06:49.99,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,If the calamity doesn't \Nstop after I kill her,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.99,0:06:51.89,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,then I'll agree with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.98,0:07:43.38,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Now, it ends.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.31,0:07:53.60,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,You're wrong...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.55,0:08:12.04,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,What's your problem? I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.70,0:08:15.43,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just trying to \Nprotect us all! So why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.34,0:08:20.71,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,If you're so desperate to die,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.71,0:08:22.60,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,I'll kill you along with her!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.03,0:08:35.66,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Stupid brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.04,0:08:38.12,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.12,0:08:38.83,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.24,0:08:41.37,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm sorry! Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.45,0:08:46.38,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.01,0:09:03.56,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You're not from Yomi North.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.56,0:09:05.89,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No. I'm from Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.56,0:09:07.49,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.77,0:09:13.28,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Are you in pain?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.36,0:09:15.58,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.54,0:09:19.16,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Someone I love died.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.06,0:09:22.37,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.07,0:09:25.54,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.54,0:09:28.00,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We're the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.24,0:10:02.94,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,A year and a half ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.17,0:10:06.47,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,I hit you with an empty can.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.02,0:10:09.00,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.88,0:10:16.96,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly, you're terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.47,0:10:22.07,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,You're supposed to say you remember,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.07,0:10:23.39,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,even if it's not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.99,0:10:28.54,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Akazawa...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.65,0:10:51.69,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Misaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.24,0:10:53.60,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Misaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.07,0:10:58.49,Default,Phone,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}August 9 (Sun.)
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.47,0:10:57.19,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! I've got a signal!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.24,0:10:58.49,Default,Phone,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Redial
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.24,0:10:58.49,Default,Phone,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Mei Misaki
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.80,0:11:01.06,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Please connect.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.50,0:11:17.64,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Sakakibara?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.64,0:11:19.49,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Misaki! Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.49,0:11:20.20,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.20,0:11:21.15,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.45,0:11:23.45,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,The back yard.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.45,0:11:24.46,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Are you hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.46,0:11:26.40,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.40,0:11:28.75,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,But, I can't really move.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.56,0:11:31.21,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm coming, okay? \NI'll be right there, so—
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.21,0:11:32.44,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Don't come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.11,0:11:34.14,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.66,0:11:38.00,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,You don't want to come here, Sakakibara.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.00,0:11:39.21,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,But why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.98,0:11:40.72,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.34,0:11:44.16,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I have to stop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.74,0:11:49.73,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Misaki, you can't mean... Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.27,0:11:52.00,Default,Misaki,0000,0000,0000,,You'll regret it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.56,0:11:53.67,Default,Misaki,0000,0000,0000,,That's why.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.24,0:12:04.45,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Misaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.39,0:12:08.56,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Misaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.20,0:12:11.91,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Stay back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.94,0:12:17.92,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,We have to help!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.92,0:12:18.84,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,We can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.32,0:12:24.34,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I see the color of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.09,0:12:28.97,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Did you just realize it now?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.69,0:12:35.10,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I've known for some time, \Nbut I couldn't tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.54,0:12:36.40,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,But now...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.01,0:12:41.36,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,It's time for me to stop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.36,0:12:41.90,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.18,0:12:48.49,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.49,0:12:51.00,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be. It can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.86,0:12:52.83,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,It's not true!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.89,0:12:55.97,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,She's the extra?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.38,0:12:58.55,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,You're sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.38,0:13:02.44,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,You're sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.20,0:13:05.43,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Mikami...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.26,0:13:08.87,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Reiko is the extra?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.32,0:13:10.50,Default,Reiko,0000,0000,0000,,Kouichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.30,0:13:13.29,Default,Reiko,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now, the fourth thing \Nyou need to know to
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.29,0:13:14.78,Default,Reiko,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}prepare yourself for Yomi North is:
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.27,0:13:22.24,Default,Reiko,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Keep the line between my\Nwork and personal roles clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.24,0:13:25.56,Default,Reiko,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Be careful not to call \Nme Reiko by mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.56,0:13:30.16,Default,Reiko,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}At school, I'm the assistant homeroom teacher, Ms. Mikami, at all times.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.16,0:13:30.95,Default,Reiko,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Got that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.64,0:13:35.91,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Does any other class in our school have \Nan assistant homeroom teacher?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.37,0:13:37.43,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.03,0:13:39.06,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,They don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.94,0:13:43.77,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,The 9th grade's class 3 is the only one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.89,0:13:48.72,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Our classroom had the right \Nnumber of desks this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.38,0:13:52.55,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,And yet the calamity began in April.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.21,0:13:54.43,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you think that is?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.26,0:13:58.56,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Because the place short one desk...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.16,0:14:01.86,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,...was the faculty room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.86,0:14:04.16,Default,Reiko,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.16,0:14:05.37,Default,Reiko,0000,0000,0000,,She's lying!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.51,0:14:10.31,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Move out of the way, Sakakibara.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.84,0:14:32.76,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,I'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.62,0:14:38.64,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,I'll send the dead back to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.29,0:14:41.56,Default,Reiko,0000,0000,0000,,Kouichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.93,0:14:44.43,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Reiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.16,0:14:48.22,Default,Reiko,0000,0000,0000,,Don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.22,0:14:49.67,Default,Reiko,0000,0000,0000,,Don't do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.05,0:14:52.19,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Is this right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.19,0:14:53.41,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Is this really right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.87,0:14:55.41,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Is this really the right choice?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.94,0:14:57.41,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There's no mistake?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.82,0:15:01.17,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If we're wrong, I'll have murdered Reiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.83,0:15:04.90,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Is everything Misaki said true?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.90,0:15:06.28,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Can I trust her?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.85,0:15:08.38,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I remembered.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.38,0:15:10.51,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I saw it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.72,0:15:12.99,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I was watching.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.28,0:15:54.89,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,A year and a half ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.89,0:15:56.95,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I saw Ms. Mikami being killed!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.85,0:16:00.23,Default,Bird,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Cheer! Cheer up!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.23,0:16:03.60,Default,Bird,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Why? Why? Rei!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.62,0:16:03.60,Default,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Certificate of Excellence Presented to Reiko Mikami
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.99,0:16:06.48,Default,Tamie,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I suppose it was about \Na year and a half ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.15,0:16:08.98,Default,Tamie,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}At the pet shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.68,0:16:12.24,Default,Yousuke,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}How does it feel to be back after a \Nyear and a half away from Yomiyama?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.86,0:16:14.50,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A year and a half ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.50,0:16:16.96,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I hit you with an empty can.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.96,0:16:17.99,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.35,0:16:22.16,Default,Ryouhei,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}After a death, there always \Nfollows a funeral.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.16,0:16:26.92,Default,Ryouhei,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}How very tired I am of funerals...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.92,0:16:32.01,Default,Ryouhei,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My poor Ritsuko... My poor Reiko, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.09,0:16:37.47,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Believe me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.66,0:17:18.85,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Reiko...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.67,0:17:24.15,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye, Reiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.91,0:17:36.64,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye, Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.07,0:17:44.83,Default,Grave,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Mikami Family Grave
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.95,0:17:54.28,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,You're here, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.33,0:17:59.52,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Everything okay with your lungs now?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.52,0:18:00.76,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.76,0:18:03.35,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Probably won't be able to \Njoin in gym class, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.35,0:18:05.10,Default,Grave(R),0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Tombstone
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.35,0:18:05.10,Default,Grave(L),0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}October 29 Reiko\NJuly 27 Ritsuko
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.21,0:18:08.51,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,None of the others remember Ms. Mikami.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.01,0:18:11.56,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Only us, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.70,0:18:18.79,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I guess she was getting worried
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.79,0:18:22.84,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,that you might become the ninth victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.66,0:18:26.34,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,So eight people died...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.17,0:18:31.04,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Strictly speaking, there were \Nten victims in August.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.41,0:18:33.70,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Who were the other two?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.70,0:18:35.29,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,The manager and his wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.47,0:18:39.34,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,They were Takabayashi's \Nmaternal grandparents.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.94,0:18:45.31,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,I'm told they were in a poor \Nemotional state since his death.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.53,0:18:50.54,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Mikami died in fall, \Na year and a half ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.69,0:18:55.28,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,She was stabbed by an unknown \Nassailant near the river.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.54,0:18:58.64,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,I can't remember, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.74,0:19:02.41,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,I hear Ms. Mikami was the \Ndead person this year?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.69,0:19:06.51,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,That means there were seven deaths
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.51,0:19:08.66,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,in the calamity two years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.66,0:19:11.79,Default,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Homeroom: Reiko Mikami  \NOctober 29, murdered
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.91,0:19:11.79,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. There were seven "X" marks.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.02,0:19:17.52,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,I saw the name "Akazawa" on \Nthe file from that year.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.11,0:19:19.00,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Was that...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.00,0:19:21.76,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, he was Akazawa's cousin,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.76,0:19:24.12,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,but they were raised more like siblings.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.86,0:19:27.63,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Shall I drive you home?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.25,0:19:30.89,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,No, we'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.30,0:19:32.48,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,All right, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.48,0:19:34.84,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Take care going home.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.68,0:19:36.91,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.91,0:19:40.33,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, I guess the calamity is over, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.31,0:19:51.25,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,When did you figure out that Reiko,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.42,0:19:53.63,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,that Ms. Mikami, was the extra?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.01,0:19:56.47,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,When was it...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.15,0:19:59.30,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.61,0:20:02.13,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you say anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.92,0:20:05.17,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,What good would it have done?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.34,0:20:08.57,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I obviously couldn't tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.10,0:20:12.10,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Mikami was special to you, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.28,0:20:14.72,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, Reiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.83,0:20:22.46,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Want to go check out \Nthat amusement park?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.46,0:20:23.32,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.27,0:20:26.83,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,The Ferris wheel.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.24,0:20:29.89,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I don't ride those.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.89,0:20:30.83,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,No?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.63,0:20:36.70,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,I tried to call your cell phone
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.59,0:20:39.54,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,from the hospital the other day,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.54,0:20:41.08,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,but I couldn't connect.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.77,0:20:43.07,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,That's because...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.91,0:20:46.30,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I threw it in the river after that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.76,0:20:47.82,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.82,0:20:49.49,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I hate those devices.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.10,0:20:52.53,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Do we really need to be \Nconnected through them, all the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.03,0:20:57.56,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,She'll probably give me \Na new one soon, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.51,0:21:00.67,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,If she does,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.67,0:21:02.03,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,can I call you sometimes?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.27,0:21:06.56,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.99,0:21:09.34,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.34,0:21:12.28,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Mochizuki gave these to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.16,0:21:15.31,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,You can see Reiko in them, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.83,0:21:16.54,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.52,0:21:19.72,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,None of them could see her.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.71,0:21:24.27,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Even Mochizuki didn't \Nrealize she was there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.82,0:21:26.09,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.40,0:21:27.78,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,What about the color?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.78,0:21:30.26,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,What color is Reiko?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.63,0:21:36.06,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I see the color of death on her.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.73,0:21:42.47,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if we'll slowly \Nforget all this over time, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.09,0:21:46.03,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,The trip, everything that's \Nhappened since April...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.18,0:21:50.34,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Everything that had \Nto do with Reiko Mikami...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.91,0:21:54.12,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Everything...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.74,0:21:59.67,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,You really don't want to forget?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.62,0:22:02.00,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,You want to remember, forever?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.25,0:22:31.66,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,It's over now, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.16,0:24:14.01,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's how to stop the calamity.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.01,0:24:17.01,Default,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}To: The Students of Grade 9, Class 3
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.49,0:24:17.65,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}How you interpret this is up to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.30,0:24:21.34,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Just make sure to carefully \Nconsider your actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.90,0:24:25.55,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Think it through, and discuss \Nit with your friends,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.98,0:24:28.79,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}so you'll have no regrets.
